Method Detail

findFrameSet

FrameSet findFrameSet(java.lang.String name,
                      FrameSetService.Callback callback)
Finds the given FrameSet, returning it immediately if available or invoking the callback when it becomes availale if if isn't at the the time of the call. The callback can be null if the caller doesn't want a callback.

loadFrameSet

FrameSet loadFrameSet(java.lang.String name,
                      java.lang.String xml_filename,
                      ServiceBroker sb,
                      BlackboardService bbs)
Creates a FrameSet with the given name, populating it from the given xml file. The given BlackboardService will be used by the FrameSet to publish Frames and modifications.

loadFrameSet

FrameSet loadFrameSet(java.lang.String name,
                      java.lang.String[] xml_filenames,
                      ServiceBroker sb,
                      BlackboardService bbs)
Creates a FrameSet with the given name, populating it from the given xml files, loaded in order. The given BlackboardService will be used by the FrameSet to publish Frames and modifications.

getNames

java.util.Set getNames()
Returns a collection of the names of the all the FrameSets known to the service.
